# Docker build context excludes — build context is the repo root (see
# backend/Dockerfile's/frontend/Dockerfile's top comments).
#
# CRITICAL: without this file, `COPY backend ./backend` / `COPY frontend
# ./frontend` copy EVERYTHING under those directories into the image layer,
# including backend/.env (real API keys: OPENAI_API_KEY, MODAL_TOKEN_ID,
# MODAL_TOKEN_SECRET, COMPOSIO_API_KEY, ...). .gitignore does NOT protect
# against this — it only stops `git add`, Docker's COPY ignores it entirely.
# A baked-in .env means every image built from this Dockerfile (and every
# layer, even after a later `RUN rm .env`) permanently contains the secrets
# that were present in .env at build time — anyone who can `docker pull` or
# `docker save`/inspect the image layers can read them back out, whether or
# not the image is ever run.

# --- Secrets — never let these into a build context ---
backend/.env
backend/.env.*
!backend/.env.example
frontend/.env
frontend/.env.*
!frontend/.env.example
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- VCS / editor ---
.git/
.github/
.claude/
.codex/
.agents/

# --- Python ---
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
backend/.venv/
backend/**/*.egg-info/

# --- Node ---
**/node_modules/
frontend/dist/

# --- Runtime data / large local artifacts (never needed inside the image) ---
backend/agent_space/
backend/logs/
artifacts/
DATA/
example/
example_doc/
requirement/

# --- Misc large / irrelevant top-level dirs not part of the image build ---
Paper2Any/
deer-flow/
next-ai-draw-io/
open-swe/
drawio-skill/
mcp/
scripts/
plans/
new/
improvement/
